US1 ‚Äî Select a signature method

As a support agent
I want to select a signature method
So that I can finalize the return process correctly

Description

On the Sign and confirm step, the agent must select one signature method before validating the process.

Available methods (initial scope):
	‚Ä¢	Sign on my own screen
	‚Ä¢	Sign on tablet

Unavailable methods (visible but disabled):
	‚Ä¢	Sign with external solution

No method is selected by default.
The Validate button is disabled until a method is selected.

Acceptance Criteria

GIVEN I am on Step 4 "Sign and confirm"
THEN all signature methods are displayed
AND no method is selected by default

GIVEN a signature method is unavailable
THEN it is visible but disabled and not selectable

GIVEN no method is selected
THEN the Validate button is disabled

WHEN I select an available signature method
THEN the Validate button becomes enabled


‚∏ª

US2 ‚Äî Sign on technician screen (on-screen signature)

As a collaborator (guided by the support agent)
I want to sign directly on the technician‚Äôs screen using my finger
So that I can validate the return without using another device

Description

When ‚ÄúSign on my own screen‚Äù is selected and the agent clicks Validate:
	‚Ä¢	A signature capture screen is displayed
	‚Ä¢	The collaborator signs using finger/touch
	‚Ä¢	The signature is rendered live in a dedicated framed area
	‚Ä¢	The agent validates to complete the process

Acceptance Criteria

GIVEN "Sign on my own screen" is selected
WHEN I click Validate
THEN a signature capture area is displayed

WHEN the collaborator draws in the signature area
THEN the signature is displayed in real time

GIVEN no signature is drawn
THEN the Validate button is disabled

WHEN a signature is present
AND I click Validate
THEN the signature is saved
AND the process moves to the completion screen


